there are guns pointed at you right now.

25:15.890 --> 25:18.848
Now, can you please lie down for me?

25:30.029 --> 25:31.690
Hold the fuck up.

25:31.906 --> 25:33.567
Am I in therapy?

25:33.783 --> 25:35.114
Well, it'S like therapy, yes.

25:35.326 --> 25:36.611
But with an incentive.

25:36.828 --> 25:38.910
I don't give a Shit what the incentive is.

25:39.122 --> 25:42.080
I am not gonna talk about my feelings.

25:42.291 --> 25:45.499
-What about the other room?
-What room are you referring to?

25:45.712 --> 25:48.624
The one where y'all
had the vampires fucking...

25:48.840 --> 25:50.922
...under that hideous fluorescent lighting.

25:51.134 --> 25:54.547
Put me in that room
and I will fuck somebody for y'all.

25:54.762 --> 25:56.718
I want out. This room's bullshit.

25:56.931 --> 25:59.718
The copulation study is for level threes.

25:59.934 --> 26:01.845
You're a level one.

26:02.061 --> 26:04.723
Our interest in you is more intellectual.

26:04.939 --> 26:07.646
We want to know what you think...

26:07.859 --> 26:10.316
...how you think, what you think about.

26:10.528 --> 26:14.112
And we will remain here
as long as it takes...

26:14.323 --> 26:17.565
...until you engage
in meaningful conversation.

26:19.620 --> 26:22.453
You mentioned something
about an incentive.

26:23.666 --> 26:25.076
When was the last time you fed?

26:25.585 --> 26:27.166
Two days ago.

26:27.378 --> 26:28.879
Good.

26:31.048 --> 26:34.040
I am going to ask you
a series of questions...

26:34.260 --> 26:36.751
...and if I deem your responses truthful...

26:36.971 --> 26:39.804
...we have what we call
a living donor program...

26:40.016 --> 26:42.678
...or LDP.

26:48.691 --> 26:52.809
And what if I don't feel like
being a good girl?

26:53.029 --> 26:56.692
You can have watered-down Tru Blood.

26:56.908 --> 26:59.490
-Care to try it?
-Bring me a donor.

26:59.702 --> 27:01.363
Male or female?

27:01.579 --> 27:02.864
Female.

27:06.250 --> 27:09.037
Send in Somchai, please.

27:10.254 --> 27:11.505
[DOOR BEEPING]

27:14.884 --> 27:18.126
Hello. My name is Somchai.

27:24.227 --> 27:27.219
First question, please.

27:27.438 --> 27:31.807
Talk to me about what value
you place on life.

27:32.026 --> 27:34.142
Human life or vampire life?

27:34.362 --> 27:36.899
Let's start with human
and then work our way up.

27:37.114 --> 27:39.947
-Who's the human?
-How about me?

27:40.159 --> 27:43.526
What value do you place on my life?

27:43.746 --> 27:46.613
-None.
-Heh.

27:46.791 --> 27:48.531
Can you expand on that?

27:48.751 --> 27:54.041
Your insignificance to me
cannot be underestimated.

27:54.257 --> 27:57.215
You are food, nothing else.

27:57.969 --> 28:00.381
Not even good food.
You reek of tuna fiSh.

28:00.555 --> 28:01.590
[CHUCKLES]

28:01.764 --> 28:05.928
Truth is, I care more about the life
of that tuna you ate...

28:06.143 --> 28:07.849
...than I care about you.

28:08.521 --> 28:09.636
Very good.

28:11.274 --> 28:12.730
Somchai.

28:23.286 --> 28:24.947
[SOMCHAI GASPS]

28:26.247 --> 28:28.533
[SNIFFS THEN MOANS]

28:35.673 --> 28:37.254
[SOMCHAI GRUNTS]

28:51.355 --> 28:52.470
Hey, sugar boo boo.

28:52.690 --> 28:55.102
Now what iS you doing here
at your place of work?

28:55.318 --> 28:56.979
Because I know it ain't work.

28:57.153 --> 29:00.065
You know that spirit thingie that appeared
out of thin air in my bathroom?

29:00.239 --> 29:02.651
-Uh-huh.
-TurnS out it wasn't a spirit.

29:02.867 --> 29:06.200
It was a fairy vampire trying to break
through a portal from another dimension.

29:09.540 --> 29:10.916
He told you he loved you?

29:12.585 --> 29:14.667
And the fucked-up part....

29:14.879 --> 29:17.120
...I kind of believed him.

29:17.340 --> 29:22.755
Ma'am, you have a messed-up talent
for finding the good in every creature you meet.

29:22.970 --> 29:25.803
But you can't be buying
what this motherfucker is selling.

29:26.015 --> 29:30.008
My whole life, I've always
known the truth.

29:30.227 --> 29:33.219
It's the curse of being able
to read people's minds.

29:34.398 --> 29:37.356
Until vampires came along,
and then I was in the dark.

29:37.568 --> 29:40.105
And I got more than
my fair share of lieS.

29:42.657 --> 29:46.696
I need to find my way back to the truth.

29:48.537 --> 29:50.698
And I'm gonna need your help to do it.

29:54.669 --> 29:58.833
Remember that time Richie-Bobby
shit himself on Sit-up 27 of 200?

29:59.006 --> 30:00.712
[LAUGHS]

30:01.384 --> 30:03.670
Why am I here, Bellefleur?

30:03.886 --> 30:06.468
You know, just to shoot the Shit
and reminisce.

30:06.681 --> 30:09.343
We could have shot the shit
and reminisced over Facebook.

30:09.558 --> 30:12.015
But you called me up out of the blue...

30:12.228 --> 30:14.059
...after how many years of not speaking?

30:14.271 --> 30:16.227
Never reaching out?

30:16.816 --> 30:19.182
I'm gonna ask you one more time.

30:19.360 --> 30:20.850
Why am I here?

30:22.571 --> 30:24.607
How'S your Shooting these days, Justin?

30:24.824 --> 30:26.360
How'S my shooting?

30:26.575 --> 30:29.032
I recall you used to
be able to fire a grouping...

30:29.245 --> 30:31.827
...that big from 50 meters out.

30:32.039 --> 30:36.157
Might be just a hair bigger than that now,
but I haven't lost much.

30:37.420 --> 30:39.536
What the fuck'S going on, Bellefleur?

30:42.174 --> 30:44.039
How would you like to kill me?

30:44.260 --> 30:45.670
What?

30:45.886 --> 30:49.253
I could pay you. It won't be much.
But you wouldn't be doing it for free.

30:49.473 --> 30:50.553
Hold the fuck on.

30:50.766 --> 30:54.634
I tried to do it myself,
but I couldn't pull the trigger.

30:54.854 --> 30:57.436
-What happened to you over there?
-It doesn't matter.

30:57.648 --> 31:00.230
All that matters iS that
I deserve to die for it.

31:00.443 --> 31:03.150
-It was war.
-We killed people. I killed people.

31:03.362 --> 31:04.397
We all did.

31:05.990 --> 31:08.402
Remember Patrick Devins?

31:08.617 --> 31:11.108
I killed him too. Just last week.

31:11.328 --> 31:13.489
Here in this bar over there at table eight.

31:14.040 --> 31:17.157
Terry, who's this?

31:17.334 --> 31:20.826
Um, Justin, this is my wife Arlene.

31:21.047 --> 31:23.083
Arlene, this is Justin McGillich.

31:23.299 --> 31:24.880
Pleased to meet you, ma'am.

31:25.092 --> 31:26.798
And how do y'all know each other?

31:27.011 --> 31:29.093
Marine Corps, basic training.

31:29.305 --> 31:31.762
And what bringS you to Merlotte's?

31:33.809 --> 31:35.640
Driving cross-country.

31:35.853 --> 31:38.970
Figured I'd look an Old buddy up
on my way.

31:40.191 --> 31:42.432
Okay. Um....

31:42.902 --> 31:45.644
Terry, I don't mean to be rude,
but Big John is pissed.

31:45.863 --> 31:47.524
Just two minutes is all I need.

31:47.740 --> 31:50.152
I'll tell him. But hurry.

31:55.331 --> 31:56.946
I take it she knows.

31:57.166 --> 31:58.952
She wants me to cover it up...

31:59.168 --> 32:02.831
...and go on like nothing ever happened.

32:03.047 --> 32:05.129
But I can't do it, Justin.

32:06.967 --> 32:08.673
I can't do it no more.

32:10.221 --> 32:12.507
Yeah, Terry. I'll kill you.

32:13.849 --> 32:16.010
But I'm not gonna take your money.

32:17.937 --> 32:19.677
I'll be doing it for free.

32:21.023 --> 32:22.809
Thank you.

32:23.734 --> 32:27.101
Uh, just give me a couple days
to get my affairs in order.

32:27.321 --> 32:29.812
After that, it's up to you.

32:31.200 --> 32:33.862
Ijust don't want to know
it'S coming, okay?

32:36.205 --> 32:38.537
Why don't you get on
back to Big John?

33:04.275 --> 33:05.606
[SIGHS]

33:05.776 --> 33:10.816
She said it was Jessica
attacked her, killed her sisters.

33:12.158 --> 33:13.648
Jessica?

33:16.078 --> 33:19.036
But she's such a nice vampire.

33:19.790 --> 33:22.076
She killed my kids, Holly.

33:23.169 --> 33:24.625
I know.

33:24.837 --> 33:27.920
Andy, I know.

33:31.260 --> 33:33.046
There's just--

33:33.262 --> 33:35.594
There's not even any words.

33:37.016 --> 33:38.881
I'm just saying--

33:39.101 --> 33:43.014
I don't know, maybe it'S
some kind of terrible accident.

33:43.230 --> 33:45.892
It wasn't no accident.

33:46.442 --> 33:49.479
She said Bill was taking their blood.

33:49.695 --> 33:51.981
Performing some kind of experiment.

33:58.370 --> 34:00.406
Andy Bellefleur, what are you doing?

34:00.623 --> 34:04.457
If Bill is behind this, I'm gonna put a wooden
bullet through his cold, dead heart.

34:04.668 --> 34:06.249
No, you are not.

34:06.462 --> 34:08.748
Bill is stronger than you, okay?

34:08.964 --> 34:12.582
You go over there half-cocked
on some macho revenge mission...

34:12.801 --> 34:16.419
...then you will lose and you will die.

34:18.474 --> 34:21.090
Then that poor little fairy girl there...

34:21.602 --> 34:23.684
...she ain't gonna have nobody.

34:39.578 --> 34:41.239
I'm calling off the search party.

34:44.708 --> 34:46.824
As far as anyone's gonna know...

34:47.044 --> 34:49.660
...those girls went back to their mama.

34:51.590 --> 34:53.581
[SOBBING]

35:00.557 --> 35:03.014
I can'tjust do nothing.

35:05.980 --> 35:07.390
Hey.

35:07.606 --> 35:09.142
We're gonna get you through this.

35:21.287 --> 35:22.402
Hey.

35:24.456 --> 35:25.616
Hey.

35:27.501 --> 35:28.786
You okay?

35:30.546 --> 35:32.207
Yeah.

35:38.095 --> 35:40.507
Sorry, I had a lot to drink last night.

35:41.765 --> 35:44.256
No need to be sorry.

35:44.601 --> 35:46.512
Sure you're Okay?

35:46.729 --> 35:50.972
I wanted to know what it'd be like
to live like a shifter.

35:51.191 --> 35:52.397
Now I know.

35:53.193 --> 35:54.649
Always on the run.

35:54.862 --> 35:57.069
Hiding who you are.

35:57.698 --> 35:59.814
Afraid you're gonna die.

36:01.327 --> 36:03.943
Hey, I'm gonna find us
a way out of this.

36:05.581 --> 36:07.572
Really?

36:08.083 --> 36:10.199
EMMA:
Sam.

36:11.545 --> 36:14.082
Hey. Hey, sweet pea.

36:18.761 --> 36:21.173
GUARD:
Pender, Jacobs, Callahan.

36:24.767 --> 36:26.007
Tara?

36:29.438 --> 36:30.894
Thank God you're here.

36:31.106 --> 36:33.188
They put me in a room
with racquetballs...

36:33.400 --> 36:34.731
...and they fucking shot me.

36:34.943 --> 36:36.558
Me too.

36:36.779 --> 36:38.565
Where are we?

36:38.781 --> 36:40.271
We're in hell.

36:40.491 --> 36:42.152
I thought so.

36:42.368 --> 36:44.404
She said I was going to hell.

36:44.620 --> 36:47.737
Steve Newlin's ex told me
I was a demon whore.

36:47.956 --> 36:49.241
What's wrong with you?

36:49.458 --> 36:52.200
I ate four fairy girls. I am so fucked up.

36:52.419 --> 36:54.626
Jesus. Come on.

37:01.720 --> 37:03.836
I feel like I'm losing my mind.

37:04.473 --> 37:05.679
Yeah.

37:09.812 --> 37:11.177
Do you believe in the devil?

37:11.397 --> 37:13.228
No.

37:13.440 --> 37:15.852
But my mom sure did.

37:16.068 --> 37:18.775
She'd see the devil in everything.

37:18.987 --> 37:22.024
Devil's on the TV, in the rock 'n' roll...

37:22.241 --> 37:24.152
...and in your heart.

37:26.412 --> 37:28.619
What if we're wrong?

37:28.831 --> 37:32.744
Bill'S trying to save vampire-kind,
but what if we don't deserve to survive?

37:32.960 --> 37:34.245
What if we're just bad?

37:34.503 --> 37:35.709
[WHISPERING]
Don't be talking crazy.

37:35.921 --> 37:37.957
I didn't have to kill those fairy girls.

37:38.173 --> 37:40.585
-But that's--
-No, don't say it was in my nature...

37:40.801 --> 37:44.214
...or that I couldn't help myself.
I killed them because I wanted to.

37:47.349 --> 37:49.305
ThiS hunger in me.

37:50.602 --> 37:53.014
It's never going away, is it?

37:58.652 --> 38:01.519
The longer vampires nest together,
the stronger the bond becomes.

38:01.738 --> 38:03.694
-But it's not a real bond.
-How so?

38:03.907 --> 38:06.023
Split up a nest one night...

38:06.243 --> 38:08.655
...the vampires that Shared it
will be staking each other the next...

38:08.871 --> 38:11.613
...if one so much as lookS
at the other one funny.

38:11.832 --> 38:14.824
So we Shouldn't worry
about regrouping vampires...

38:15.043 --> 38:18.501
...from barracks to barracks
to prevent relationships from forming?

38:18.714 --> 38:21.626
I don't give a fuck what you worry about.

38:21.842 --> 38:23.503
But I agree.

38:23.719 --> 38:25.255
Your worries would be unfounded.

38:25.471 --> 38:28.634
Thank you, Pam. You're on.

38:28.849 --> 38:31.386
Actually, Somchai, you can relax.

38:31.602 --> 38:33.183
I'm feeling a little full.

38:33.395 --> 38:36.137
So under ordinary circumstances, then...

38:36.356 --> 38:40.474
...you feel no remorse when
you kill another vampire?

38:40.694 --> 38:42.025
No, I don't.

38:42.237 --> 38:46.071
Are you Speaking
for yourself or for all vampires?

38:46.283 --> 38:49.525
I like to think of myself
as especially unremorseful.

38:49.745 --> 38:52.031
But I doubt any of us gives a fuck.

38:52.247 --> 38:54.454
Well, except for when
it comes to your maker.

38:54.666 --> 38:57.203
Yeah, that's a different story.

38:58.754 --> 39:01.291
Tell me about your maker, Pam.

39:01.507 --> 39:03.338
What was his name?

39:04.635 --> 39:06.341
Her name?

39:06.553 --> 39:08.635
Does it matter?
He's not my maker anymore.

39:08.847 --> 39:11.224
-He released me.
-And how does that work?

39:11.433 --> 39:14.846
You say the words
"As your maker, I release you" and it's done.

39:15.062 --> 39:16.177
Just like that?

39:16.563 --> 39:18.064
[SIGHS]

39:23.195 --> 39:25.902
Did you have any idea it was coming?

39:26.114 --> 39:27.945
None.

39:28.825 --> 39:30.156
What did it feel like?

39:31.161 --> 39:34.153
I feel nothing.

39:34.706 --> 39:35.991
Nothing?

39:40.796 --> 39:44.414
You humans love your pain, don't you?

39:44.633 --> 39:47.249
You just love being in it.

39:47.469 --> 39:49.881
You even consider it a virtue.

39:50.347 --> 39:52.383
Cry the most at a funeral...

39:52.599 --> 39:54.590
...you must be the best person.

39:54.810 --> 39:56.516
You promise to never forget.

39:56.728 --> 40:00.061
You promise to feel
the sting of loss forever.

40:00.274 --> 40:05.894
Because for y'all,
forever is just the blink of an eye.

40:06.113 --> 40:08.946
Your liveS are pathetically brief.

40:10.033 --> 40:13.821
When we say forever,
we have to mean it.

40:14.037 --> 40:17.245
So we move past our pain.

40:17.457 --> 40:19.789
We heal, we move on.

40:20.002 --> 40:23.039
Because pain is a worthless emotion.

40:25.841 --> 40:30.551
For a time, my maker
was everything to me.

40:30.762 --> 40:32.218
He released me.

40:33.599 --> 40:35.305
It hurt.

40:37.853 --> 40:40.811
But now...

40:41.523 --> 40:42.854
...I'm over it.

40:43.066 --> 40:45.057
He's nobody to me.

40:45.277 --> 40:49.361
I'm not sure I believe you.

40:51.199 --> 40:55.067
Looks like you and I
are through, then, Somchai.

40:58.790 --> 41:00.781
[COINS CLATTERING]

41:01.918 --> 41:03.533
[DIALING ON PHONE]

41:03.712 --> 41:05.703
[LINE RINGING]

41:07.132 --> 41:09.088
MAN [ON MESSAGE]:
Hi, you've reached the Wright residence.

41:09.968 --> 41:11.299
-What the hell?
-Sorry.

41:11.511 --> 41:13.126
I can't let you do that.

41:13.347 --> 41:15.258
